# Propulsion Section — CAD Assembly & Internal Ballistics Validation

## Overview

The propulsion subsystem consists of a steel motor case, ablative insulation liner, dual-grain boost-sustain assembly (finocyl boost + BATES sustain), forward and aft closures, and a De Laval nozzle. All components were designed to fit within the fixed 100mm body tube OD while providing realistic internal ballistics validated in openMotor. The design maintains consistency with the overall missile simulation pipeline.

