## Grain Geometry

### Boost Grain (Grain 1) — Finocyl

| Parameter | Value |
|---|---|
| Type | Finocyl |
| Length | 180mm |
| Core diameter | 38mm |
| Fins | 6 × 8mm width × 10mm length |
| Inhibited ends | Both |
| Web thickness | ~14mm |
| Mass | ~1.30 kg |

### Sustain Grain (Grain 2) — BATES

| Parameter | Value |
|---|---|
| Type | BATES (cylindrical bore, no fins) |
| Length | 416mm |
| Core diameter | 38mm |
| Inhibited ends | Both |
| Web thickness | ~23mm |
| Mass | ~3.14 kg |

The boost grain uses a finocyl geometry — smaller core and fins for high initial burning surface area, producing the peak thrust phase. The sustain grain uses a BATES geometry — plain cylindrical bore with no fins — which produces a neutral burn profile (approximately constant surface area as the grain regresses). This matches the Project 06 constant 800N sustain thrust assumption more accurately than a finned geometry. The boost-sustain dual-grain architecture is standard in tactical missile motors.

