### Nozzle Tradeoff vs. Project 03

Project 03 validated nozzle CFD methodology at Ae/A* = 16.67 under unconstrained demonstration conditions (P₀ = 9.8 MPa, T₀ = 3710 K). For the tactical motor, the exit diameter is limited to 60mm to fit inside the 100mm body tube OD fixed by Project 04. At a 25mm throat, Ae/A* = 16.67 would require a ~102mm exit — exceeding the body diameter. The chosen Ae/A* = 5.76 is a practical sea-level packaging tradeoff that maintains positive thrust coefficient. Project 03 remains a valid high-fidelity CFD reference independent of the tactical motor packaging constraints.

