## Limitations

**0-D ballistics model.** openMotor uses a lumped-parameter approach. Full 3-D erosive burning, slag accumulation, and grain deformation are not modeled.

**Propellant approximation.** The custom HTPB/AP/Al entry is representative of the propellant class but not calibrated to a specific certified formulation. Real tactical propellant data is export-controlled.

**Static sea-level conditions.** Chamber pressure and thrust are computed at sea-level ambient (101325 Pa). Altitude effects on delivered thrust are captured in Project 06 trajectory integration.

**Ignition transients.** openMotor assumes instantaneous full-surface ignition. Start-up transients and tail-off behavior are approximated.

**Minor warnings.** Peak mass flux warning was observed but does not affect positive thrust production or simulation validity.

